# Models Overview

This folder contains the core scientific and mathematical models of the Open Earth Polar Model. Each model offers a theoretical and computational framework for understanding Earth’s motion, energy fields, and curvature dynamics.

## Included Models

- `polar_axis_model.md`: Earth's rotation centered around the polar axis
- `time_curvature_model.md`: Gravity and energy interactions as functions of time-curved fields
- `orbital_rotation_model.md`: Combined orbital and rotational effects in Earth-Sun-Moon system
- `simulation_notes.md`: Assumptions and computational considerations for simulating the models

## Diagrams

The `/diagrams/` subfolder contains visuals used to support the models.

These models are open for critique, enhancement, and simulation contributions.
